 NVDA SPCX and TSLA</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Why Marvell (MRVL) looks =
"Marvelous" and will be a trillion-dollar market cap in the coming years ak=
a a 4x. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">When Matt Murphy became CEO, the com=
pany was stuck making low-margin chips for hard drives, printers, and toys =
=E2=80=94 exactly the wrong place as the cloud and AI era began. He killed =
those businesses and went all-in on data infrastructure. That single decisi=
on changed everything. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Marvell went on a sma=
rt shopping spree:</p><ul><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Cavium (network pr=
ocessors)</p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Avera (IBM=E2=80=99s custo=
m chip team =E2=80=94 unlocked Amazon, Microsoft, Google deals)</p></li><li=
><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Inphi (optical tech)</p></li><li><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:10px 0">Innovium (Ethernet switching)</p></li><li><p style=3D"margin:1=
0px 0">Celestial AI (photonic fabric inside the chip package)</p></li></ul>=
<p style=3D"margin:10px 0">He made some very clever acquisitions to positio=
n MRVL perfectly for the AI explosion. NVDA saw this also and invested $2 b=
illion into the company as part of a strategic partnership. When the king o=
f AI publicly backs you like that, you know it is synergistic </p><h3>The S=
ecret Sauce - They=E2=80=99re Solving AI=E2=80=99s Biggest Bottleneck</h3><=
p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Right now, AI scaling is limited by connectivity,=
 not compute or memory. You can have the best chips in the world, but if th=
ey can=E2=80=99t talk to each other fast enough, the whole system slows dow=
n. Marvell specializes in making chips communicate at insane speeds. Enter =
Photonics, traditional copper wires inside servers get slow and hot when da=
ta has to travel. Marvell=E2=80=99s technology uses light (optics) instead.=
 Light moves data faster, farther, and with less power. This is the key to =
building much larger, more efficient AI systems.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px=
 0">Nvidia=E2=80=99s upcoming Vera Rubin platform is using Marvell=E2=80=99=
s Spectrum-X Ethernet Photonics =E2=80=94 the first co-packaged optics swit=
ch in commercial production. This isn=E2=80=99t =E2=80=9Cmaybe someday=E2=
=80=9D =E2=80=94 it=E2=80=99s happening now. I reckon NVDA could even end u=
p acquiring Marvell in the future. </p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">PS SpaceX=
 and Tesla are already signed up to buy 20% of all VERA RUBINS....which mea=
ns they are also buying Marvell tech. </p><h2>Final note, TAM &amp; Mkt Siz=
e</h2><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">The optical interconnect market alone is p=
rojected to hit $200 billion per year by the end of the decade. But if Marv=
ell=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cdata center without distance=E2=80=9D vision becomes=
 reality, their addressable market becomes every single connection inside e=
very data center on Earth. That=E2=80=99s a much, much larger TAM.</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin:10px 0">h.t Sanjay for the inspiration. </p><p style=3D"margi=
n:10px 0"></p><p></p></div></td></tr>
